news.title: Noida: RG Residency residents rally against AOA, seek fresh polls
news.para: According to the residents, the current AOA executive body was formed without any general body meeting. But, the AOA refuted the allegations as false and asserted that they have been fighting for the overall benefit of the housing society.

news.title: Bombay HC refuses to stay eviction of occupants from nine illegal buildings in Thane
news.para: A bench of Chief Justice Dipankar Datta and Justice M S Karnik said it did not want citizens to live a life fraught with the risk of their buildings collapsing during the rains.

news.title: Structural audit of high rise, two-decade old buildings priority: Delhi government to HC
news.para: ​The state government said it had been decided in a meeting chaired by the chief secretary that quality and calculation test checks may be carried out on a sample basis in respect of high-rise private and government buildings having high footfall or occupancy by the concerned local bodies.

news.title: Greater Noida development body razes buildings on floodplains of Hindon River
news.para: According to the Authority, it has also filed a complaint with the police for lodging FIR and taking legal action against the offenders involved in encroachment of the land.

news.title: Builder gets bail in DHFL case days after Rs 4 crore deposit
news.para: The prosecution had opposed the bail plea, submitting that mere depositing of the amount per se did not not give Tandon the right to seek bail.

news.title: Former Solicitor General buys Rs 85-crore bungalow in Delhi
news.para: "Sunder Nagar has seen a spate of transactions due to proximity to central Delhi and most of the bungalows in the locality are built on 867 sq. yard plots. Shortage of houses or plots for sale, along with rising demand, will keep prices in the neighbourhood exceptionally high, even if rates in other parts of Delhi fluctuate," said Pradeep Prajapati, a property expert.

news.title: Registration of new realty projects rises 25% in first half of 2022: UP RERA
news.para: ​According to the Uttar Pradesh Real Estate Regulatory Authority (UP RERA), it has received 125 applications for new project registration till June 2022. In the first half of 2021, the UP RERA had received 100 such applications.

news.title: Our priority is Amrapali home buyers get their flats and their claims: SC
news.para: It said thereafter it would consider the claims of authorities like NOIDA and Greater Noida and then it would consider the claims of other statutory bodies/institutions like the electricity board or drinking water departments.

news.title: China urges banks to support property sector after mortgage boycott
news.para: The China Banking and Insurance Regulatory Commission (CBIRC) told the official industry newspaper on Sunday that banks should meet developers' financing needs where reasonable.

news.title: Construction waste plant still a dream for Ludhiana smart city
news.para: ​The project is planned under smart city mission, and officials claimed that work was going to start at the site in Dhandhari soon.

news.title: Delhi court upholds conviction of Ansal brothers for evidence tampering
news.para: Besides Ansals, the court had also awarded 7-year jail terms to former court staff Dinesh Chand Sharma and two others -- P P Batra and Anoop Singh -- and had imposed a fine of three lakh rupees each on them.

news.title: HeidelbergCement India's profit falls 25% to Rs 52 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: However, revenue from operation increased 6.10 per cent to Rs 589.89 crore during the quarter under review from Rs 555.94 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Assam: 71 houses demolished on second day in Karimganj
news.para: The administration carried out the drive to clear atleast 1,200 bighas of government and ceiling-surplus land in Ichabeel tea estate, owned by the state-run Assam Tea Corporation (ATC), and neighbouring areas which were encroached by the families without valid documents.

news.title: Prestige Group's sales bookings jump four-fold to Rs 3,012 crore
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Bengaluru-based Prestige Group said it has registered sales of Rs 3,012.1 crore, of which the Mumbai region has contributed Rs 737.8 crore.

news.title: Patta camps to follow ward-wise survey: Rajasthan minister
news.para: Khachariyawas was addressing a meeting at the secretariat on Sunday to resolve the problems being faced regarding the leases being given under the campaign in areas under Jaipur Municipal Corporation-Heritage.
